reviews.text: The food is delicious and the price is affordable but the staff is not polite. There is English menu and the staff can speak English fluently.

The food might be cheap, but be prepared for small portions, tasteless dishes, and apathetic customer service. I have visited Yoshinoya in other countries, and the Hong Kong branches are quite noticeably not up to par. The more locations they open across Hong Kong, the lower their standard of quality sinks. Yoshinoya needs to do a much better job creating a good dining experience for customers.
